The CLI experience itself covers a wide range of developer workflows. Copilot CLI can explain shell commands, suggest fixes for errors, translate natural language into complex command sequences, and help developers navigate unfamiliar codebases — all from the terminal. For teams working in hardened environments where GUI tooling is limited or disallowed, the terminal-first approach is a natural fit.

> Bring Your Own Key support means AI-assisted development no longer requires a tradeoff between developer productivity and data control.

One of the most compelling use cases is in the "develop low, deploy high" pattern common in DoD software delivery. Developers write and test code in lower-classification environments, then promote artifacts through a secure pipeline to higher-classification networks. With BYOK, each environment can have its own isolated model endpoint and key configuration, so Copilot assistance is available at every stage of that pipeline without cross-domain key exposure.

